        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 10:14PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 1014 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Anadarko, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chickasha, Anadarko, Cyril, Verden, Cement, Amber, Pocasset, Norge,
Lake Chickasha, Ninnekah, Stecker, and Laverty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
